    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential integer overflow in F1AP UE Context Release Command decoding\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_ue_context_rel_cmd` function in the F1AP library was vulnerable to integer overflow when processing malformed UE Context Release Command messages. The function used a simple loop counter without validating the protocolIEs list count, which could lead to excessive iterations or buffer overreads.\n\nThis fix adds bounds checking to validate the protocolIEs list count before entering the processing loop. Invalid count values (negative or excessively large) are now rejected early, preventing potential denial-of-service scenarios.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_ue_context.c`: Added bounds validation for protocolIEs list count in `decode_ue_context_rel_cmd`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Send a UE Context Release Command message with an extremely large protocolIEs list count\n2. Observe that the decoder enters a long-running loop attempting to process invalid entries\n3. System may become unresponsive or crash due to excessive CPU usage or memory access violations\n\nThe fix prevents this by rejecting messages with invalid count values before processing begins.\n"
}